      Methods in plt.utils that return types with arguments of type Preference 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      static java.util.List<Preference> Preference.listToPairWisePreference(int[] list)
      Given a list of preference for example (A,B,C) where the first is the most preferred, it returns a list of pair wise preference (for example A > B, C > B, A > C) as vector of pair (example [[B,A],[B,C],[C,A]]) where the second element of each pair is the most preferred (example [C,A] means that A is preferred over C)
